- 'large structure' refers to a class; 
- 'purely theoretical' refers to pure virtual methods; 
- 'components' refer to method definitions; 
- 'more specific blueprints' refer to derived classes.

sql:
SELECT class_name
FROM classes
ORDER BY class_name;

external_knowledge:
still in the conceptual phase refers to abstract classes (is_abstract = 1); 
lengthy instructions refer to descriptions with more than 50 characters; 
have been built upon refers to classes with overridden methods in their derived classes (is_overridden = 1).

sql:
SELECT class_id, AVG(sizeof_value) AS average_size
FROM sizeof
GROUP BY class_id;

SELECT sizeof_value, alignment
FROM sizeof
WHERE class_id = 1 AND member_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Classes without a parent class are considered root classes; 
- The level of a class in the hierarchy indicates its distance from the root class; 
- Access control rules define the permissions (e.g., read, write, execute) a user has for a particular class.
